We must not let Putin determine the course of action we take to provide military assistance to the Ukrainians.  

The denial of MiGs is a major misstep in the effort to support Ukraine.

The decision to reverse course on sending the MiGs to Ukraine by the Biden Administration emboldens Putin, reduces the capability of Ukrainians to defend themselves and is a complete capitulation to threats made by Putin.

This decision, in coordination with other economic sanctions, should deliver a crippling blow to the Russian economy.  

Today’s decision regarding trading status is by no means an adequate substitute for providing Ukraine with MiG-29 fighter jets to defend their homeland.

Very much support President Biden and the G7 leaders’ decision to terminate Most Favored Nation (MFN) trading status with Russia.  

This is another step in the right direction which should have been done earlier.
